
    “We need counselling, all of us. We can be cured.”This was what Refiloe Wa Ga Khunou, a cultural expert from Alexandra, Joburg and many others told the SunTeam when asked about recent violent incidents that have made headlines.Wendy Mkhonza (40) from Meadowlands in Soweto said it felt like people in Mzansi fought almost every day, while Samuel Mabaso (35) from Tembisa, Ekurhuleni said the nation needed to unite in prayer.Among the incidents of violence that have recently shocked people across the country are:A video of church members in Joburg beating up a Metro cop that went viral. The cop was attacked after trying to tow a church member’s car.In August, footage of a man and a woman being beaten by a group of white men in Montana, Tshwane was posted on Twitter.A video of former deputy minister of higher education Mduduzi Manana beating up a woman at Cubana restaurant also went viral in August. The Randburg Magistrates Court in Joburg ordered him to pay a fine of R100 000 and complete 500 hours of community service.In September, a man was filmed hitting a woman over the head many times with a spanner at an Engen garage.A video of a taxi driver assaulting a woman went viral in June.A number of videos of school kids fighting also did the rounds this year.In another incident, a scuffle between children in the play area at Spur led to their parents swearing and insulting each other.Footage of a group of white men attacking a black man outside Mugg and Bean in Randfontein, Gauteng went viral last month.Taxi driver :https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TEin_nNIVXwSchool fight: http://www.dailysun.co.za/News/National/watch-norkem-park-high-pupils-fight-20170818Manana https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AmTmQGwjqhcDJ assaulting a woman: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ME-nK6B0gtsKFC assault: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wtXUKu5fD8AChurch members assault a police: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g5QBx2skKH0Spur incident: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QVWkszB973UMugg and Bea